411
00:11:58,350 --> 00:11:59,110
Seriously...

412
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:01,840
Failed again.

413
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:03,520
One more try.

414
00:12:03,540 --> 00:12:07,100
(Third version)

415
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:07,880
Another one.

416
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:09,000
(Fourth version)

417
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,350
The paper got a bit wet.

418
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:14,110
Why can't I get that perspective right?

419
00:12:14,590 --> 00:12:15,110
I'll try again.

420
00:12:15,110 --> 00:12:17,780
(Fifth version)

421
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:23,900
(Super serious)

422
00:12:25,570 --> 00:12:26,710
Why does it look like a drumstick?

423
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:31,710
It really looks like a drumstick.

424
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:33,550
How did I end up drawing a drumstick?

425
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:35,550
(Yang's Universal Drumstick)

426
00:12:35,590 --> 00:12:36,440
Whatever.

427
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:36,910
This works.

428
00:12:37,350 --> 00:12:38,760
Then I'll color it blue.

429
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:48,400
Done.

430
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:50,440
All finished.

431
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:53,580
